<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-99] SocketServer.scala does not enforce a maximum request size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-99</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The socket server should enforce a max request size to avoid running out of memory if a large request is sent. I see code in BoundedByteBufferReceive and in KafkaConfig to specify this, but it doesn&apos;t seem to be getting used. I added this in and added a stand-alone test for the socket server to start handling some of this stuff.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
